title: Grateful Dead Live at Hampton Coliseum on 1986-03-20

description:
Set 1

Touch Of Grey, Little Red Rooster, Friend Of The Devil, It's All Over Now, Row Jimmy, Me & My Uncle-> Mexicali Blues, Althea, Box Of Rain

Set 2

Iko Iko-> Estimated Prophet-> Eyes Of The World-> Drums-> Wharf Rat-> Throwing Stones-> Not Fade Away, E: U.S. Blues

First Box of Rain since 07-28-73

reviews.review_text: Another amazing night! Cold front makes for wet and chilly night, gooney birds make for a wide open and magical one!  Great Althea and Box, simply amazing and powerful performance.

Opening the Box It may not be the most amazing setlist, or the most inspired playing but when they broke out Box of Rain the crowd went ballistic, once they realized what was being played. It had been a very long time since the last box and you can hear the energy and disbelief that comes through as the opening notes of Box begin. 

Hampton was always a great venue, especially because it was my home venue. This was a good run of shows in 86 and definitely worth a listen, if only for the Box.
